A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, so I pretended I was just working from home, actually editing "Can't Help Myself".
If only this damn file would open. (OneDrive is really fucking terrible.)
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Great.
I turned the air purifier to maximum, but it felt a bit too aggressive. However, I did smell sawdust, so doing that wasn't completely inappropriate, especially since he反对戴口罩。而且我确实需要保护自己，不是吗？）
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can only do that after he leaves.
The good news is, Chapter Four is finally finished!
Chapter Five is very long and super anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing…➡️ellipsis, there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But I still need to stick to this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repair worker is using a vacuum cleaner to clean up, hoping this means he is nearly done.
He went out (sound like) cutting something. I took a sneak peek at the progress. There is still a lot to do :(<s>
Chapter Five has 7 pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript status is quite good, mainly with adjustments in formatting, and some small modifications on active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break, a cup of tea, while that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Fingers crossed, that's a good sign.
The floor repair worker left the kitchen!
He told me that he quoted the price for fixing the entire floor, but the landlord is too tight-fisted and only agrees to pay for the area by the door where the floor is already rotten. That feels much better.
I'm having tea in the garden while the air purifier in the kitchen works hard to clean the air in the room!
